{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/pullrequests/79/comments/37959602.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/srcsim/diff/osrf/srcsim:61cc71525f32..0512e7fc6fbb?path=src%2FTask.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/pull-requests/79/_/diff#comment-37959602"}}, "parent": {"id": 37924360, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/pullrequests/79/comments/37924360.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/pull-requests/79/_/diff#comment-37924360"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 79, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/pullrequests/79.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/pull-requests/79"}}, "title": "Re-harness"}, "content": {"raw": "The lock was protecting `this->current`, to make sure it doesn't change while we're checking it. That variable wasn't being used by the derived classes, so I made it private in 78b19fe.\n\nWe could add a mutex to Skip(), but it would need to be a recursive mutex, since both Start and Update call that.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The lock was protecting <code>this-&gt;current</code>, to make sure it doesn't change while we're checking it. That variable wasn't being used by the derived classes, so I made it private in <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/commits/78b19fe\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">78b19fe</a>.</p>\n<p>We could add a mutex to Skip(), but it would need to be a recursive mutex, since both Start and Update call that.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-05-31T21:07:35.433323+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-4